Description:
Studio apartment in the Vaughn Place at McLean Gardens complex available for $1,850/month beginning November 1. With its hardwood floors, a private balcony overlooking Wisconsin Avenue, and a recently refurbished kitchen, you’ll feel at home in this 500+ square foot unit in no time. Ideal for young professionals and graduate/professional students. 
Amenities include:
* 	Central air/heat;
* 	In-unit washer/dryer;
* 	Granite countertops, garbage disposal, and stainless steel appliances;
* 	Gated, off-street parking for one vehicle (included in rent); 
* 	Water/sewer and trash collection (included in rent);
* 	24-hour concierge service; 
* 	Free rush hour shuttle service to Tenleytown Metro Station; 
* 	Full onsite fitness center; and
* 	Summertime pool facilities.
Conveniently located within walking distance of three Red Line Metro Stations (Tenleytown, Van Ness/UDC, and Cleveland Park), Capital Bikeshare, and multiple bus lines, and only a short distance from American University, Georgetown University (main campus), UDC School of Law, and Howard School of Law.
And enjoy some of D.C.’s most popular restaurants like 2Amy’s, Barcelona Wine Bar, Raku, Cactus Cantina, Café Ole, La Piquette, and Café Deluxe, as well as the new Cathedral Heights Giant, all just a short walk away. Plus D.C.’s first Wegmans coming soon to the old Fannie Mae campus.
Minimum 1-year rental period. Security deposit and first month’s rent due at signing of lease. In-person tour and credit check required. Contact Matt at matt_perdoni@yahoo.com to schedule an appointment.

